WEBVTT

00:14.380 --> 00:15.580
CHAPTER VI.

00:16.800 --> 00:21.880
And I saw when the Lamb opened one of the seals, and I heard as it were the noise of

00:21.880 --> 00:26.720
thunder one of the four beasts saying, Come and see!

00:26.720 --> 00:33.900
And I saw, and behold, a white horse, and he that sat on him had a bow, and a crown

00:33.900 --> 00:37.980
was given unto him, and he went forth conquering and to conquer.

00:38.480 --> 00:45.040
And when he had opened the second seal, I heard the second beast say, Come and see!

00:45.620 --> 00:50.880
And there went out another horse that was red, and power was given to him that sat thereon

00:50.880 --> 00:55.060
to take peace from the earth, and that they should kill one another.

00:55.610 --> 00:58.460
And there was given unto him a great sword.

00:59.380 --> 01:05.340
And when he had opened the third seal, I heard the third beast say, Come and see!

01:05.740 --> 01:12.420
And I beheld, and lo, a black horse, and he that sat on him had a pair of balances in

01:12.420 --> 01:13.080
his hand.

01:13.700 --> 01:19.520
And I heard a voice in the midst of the four beasts say, A measure of wheat for a penny,

01:19.520 --> 01:25.540
and three measures of barley for a penny, and see thou hurt not the oil and the wine.

01:26.340 --> 01:32.000
And when he had opened the fourth seal, I heard the voice of the fourth beast say, Come

01:32.000 --> 01:32.840
and see!

01:33.360 --> 01:40.820
And I looked, and behold, a pale horse, and his name that sat on him was Death, and Hell

01:40.820 --> 01:46.420
followed with him, and power was given unto them over the fourth part of the earth to

01:46.420 --> 01:51.700
kill with sword, and with hunger, and with death, and with the beasts of the earth.

01:52.440 --> 01:58.100
And when he had opened the fifth seal, I saw under the altar the souls of them that were

01:58.100 --> 02:02.040
slain for the word of God, and for the testimony which they held.

02:02.640 --> 02:09.080
And they cried with a loud voice, saying, How long, O Lord, holy and true dost thou

02:09.080 --> 02:12.560
not judge and avenge our blood on them that dwell on the earth?

02:13.140 --> 02:18.260
And white robes were given unto every one of them, and it was said unto them that they

02:18.260 --> 02:23.300
should rest yet for a little season, until their fellow-servants also, and their brethren

02:23.300 --> 02:26.480
that should be killed as they were, should be fulfilled.

02:27.320 --> 02:33.280
And I beheld when he had opened the sixth seal, and lo, there was a great earthquake,

02:33.660 --> 02:39.700
and the sun became black as sackcloth of hair, and the moon became as blood, and the stars

02:39.700 --> 02:45.480
of heaven fell unto the earth, even as a fig-tree casteth her untimely figs when she is shaken

02:45.480 --> 02:51.000
of a mighty wind, and the heaven departed as a scroll when it is rolled together, and

02:51.000 --> 02:54.220
every mountain and island were moved out of their places.

02:54.880 --> 03:00.140
And the kings of the earth, and the great men, and the rich men, and the chief captains,

03:00.300 --> 03:05.440
and the mighty men, and every bondman, and every freeman, hid themselves in the dens

03:05.440 --> 03:11.600
and in the rocks of the mountains, and said to the mountains and rocks, Foul on us, and

03:11.600 --> 03:16.400
hide us from the face of him that sitteth on the throne, and from the wrath of the Lamb,

03:16.780 --> 03:21.780
for the great day of his wrath is come, and who shall be able to stand?

